# MASTER PROMPT — MTK GALLERY BUILDER

Act as a senior Vanilla JavaScript application architect and production UI/UX engineer.

Build a complete gallery application named `mtk-gallery` for selling hand-painted artwork.

Use this repository as the base:

[NYCMEL/nala-website](https://github.com/NYCMEL/nala-website.git?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

Use ALL wc utility functionality including:

* `wc-include`
* `wc.publish`
* `wc.subscribe`
* `wc.log`
* event helpers

from this file:

[_wc.js](https://github.com/NYCMEL/nala-website/blob/main/js/_wc.js?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

---

# OUTPUT RULES

* Return ONLY one downloadable ZIP file named exactly: `x.zip`
* Never show code in chat
* Never return patch files or diffs
* Always return complete files only
* Never modify anything outside the scope of this request
* Never generate placeholder explanations instead of files
* Never create images unless explicitly requested

---

# REQUIRED FILES

Generate exactly these files:

* mtk-gallery.config.js
* mtk-gallery.scss
* mtk-gallery.html
* mtk-gallery.js
* index.html

Only create additional files if absolutely required for functionality.

---

# CORE TECH RULES

* Vanilla JavaScript only
* No frameworks
* No Bootstrap
* No React
* No Vue
* No Angular
* No external libraries
* No inline JavaScript
* No inline styles
* SCSS only
* Never compile SCSS globally except local runtime CSS file for browser loading
* index.html MUST load CSS and NEVER SCSS directly
* Never use iframes
* Use:

```html
<wc-include href="..."></wc-include>
```

---

# COMPONENT ARCHITECTURE

Component wrapper:

```html
<mtk-gallery class="mtk-gallery"></mtk-gallery>
```

Rules:

* Root class must be `.mtk-gallery`
* Scope ALL styles under `.mtk-gallery`
* No global styles
* No global IDs
* Use semantic HTML only
* ADA compliant
* Keyboard accessible
* responsive design
* Visible focus states required

---

# CONFIG + DATA RULES

ALL UI-driven data MUST come from:

`mtk-gallery.config.js`

Paintings must support:

* title
* description
* image
* price
* availability
* dimensions
* medium
* category
* PayPal data

Store owner must be able to:

* change paintings
* change prices
* change availability
* change images
* change details

from either:

* config file
* SQLite database

---

# EVENT SYSTEM RULES

Wait for `<mtk-gallery>` to exist before initializing because it may load dynamically through `<wc-include>`.

Requirements:

* Subscribe to all `4-mtk-gallery` events using `wc.subscribe`
* Create `onMessage()` handler
* Publish actions using `wc.publish`
* Log ALL payloads using `wc.log` BEFORE publishing
* Prevent duplicate initialization
* Prevent recursive render loops
* Never wipe the DOM after initialization
* Prevent blinking screen behavior
* Ensure render happens once unless explicitly refreshed

---

# GALLERY UI

Header title:

`Madam Mina's Artwork`

Layout requirements:

* `.mtk-gallery` background = `#FFF`
* `.mtk-gallery__shell`

  * `max-inline-size: 1200px`

Home screen:

* display painting cards only
* NO buttons on cards

Painting click behavior:

* opens full-page detail view
* detail view includes:

  * image
  * title
  * description
  * price
  * availability
  * dimensions
  * medium
  * actions
* include circular close button with “X”

---

# SALES + REQUEST FLOWS

## Available Paintings

Show:

* Buy with PayPal
* “Make a counter offer” link

Behavior:

* clicking link reveals counter-offer form
* form hidden by default

## Unavailable Paintings

Show:

* “Request a similar painting” link

Behavior:

* clicking link reveals request form
* form hidden by default

---

